tid":2423268,"uid":177089,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"2446db615b5d7a569971d10ec4d84a38dc63dcdb","tid":2423268,"uid":59799,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-02-25T23:33:02.000Z","msg":"好撚彩48走咗<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-02-25T23:34:26.000Z","msg":"依家係入巿時機<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/dying.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/dying.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/dying.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-02-25T23:38:33.000Z","msg":"試飛成功前都係特價<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/wail2.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/wail2.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/wail2.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"5c8d94d57d76440dc2bd8dc0cdfd47a273bca6bd","tid":2423268,"uid":609,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-02-25T23:39:19.000Z","msg":"唉屌，均價$48 走唔走好"},{"pid":"5c91dcd4fef9f7b0629e3d55f67b2057cb4ee728","tid":2423268,"uid":177089,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"5c8d94d57d76440dc2bd8dc0cdfd47a273bca6bd","tid":2423268,"uid":609,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-02-25T23:39:19.000Z","msg":"唉屌，均價$48 走唔走好"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-02-25T23:40:46.000Z","msg":"係走都唔係依家走<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2lny/donno.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"97c181919e835a70401f4b1358173ac40413c2fc","tid":2423268,"uid":177089,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-02-25T23:46:18.000Z","msg":"<span class=\"xx-large\">維珍銀河可望成為航天界巴郡</span><br />\n<br />\n由1964年首次收購一家瀕臨破產的紡織製造商到今日， 巴菲特將巴郡（NYSE:BRK.A）（NYSE:BRK.B）打造成由多間小型獨立公司組成的業界龍頭。維珍銀河（NYSE:SPCE) 能夠有朝一日成為類似的控股公司，在航天界開創類似的企業品牌帝國嗎？<br />\n<br />\n<span class=\"red\">筆者認為能夠，事實上，如果你研究一下其創辦人兼英國億萬富翁布蘭遜（Sir Richard Branson）的履歷，就更加覺得可能性很大。</span><br />\n<br />\n布蘭遜的經營方式（以及維珍銀河可能採用的經營方式）<br />\n<br />\n與巴菲特不同的是，布蘭遜和他的傘形公司維珍集團（成立於1970年，比巴郡晚六年）往往從內至外或從零開始發展業務，而不是收購別人的公司，然後把它們納入麾下。維珍還傾向於時不時地分拆及/或出售旗下公司，而巴郡就很少這樣做，舉例而言，維珍唱片是布蘭遜的首批維珍公司之一，現在則屬於環球音樂集團旗下，還有維珍大賣場在倒閉之前便被賣掉。<br />\n<br />\n但雖然如此，維珍持有的公司仍然多於它售出的公司，現時，它旗下的子公司涉足度假（維珍假日）、音樂（維珍廣播）、銀行（維珍貨幣）以及許多其他行業，當然還包括衛星發射（維珍軌道）及太空旅遊（維珍銀河）。<br />\n<br />\n航天界第一間上市的公司？<br />\n<br />\n2004年，布蘭遜在維珍航空的成功基礎上創立了維珍銀河，目標是尋找更經濟實惠的方式，讓乘客飛得更高&mdash;&mdash;飛到太空的邊緣。<br />\n<br />\n雖然其他公司可能較先擁有開辦太空旅行航班的想法（美國私人太空公司Blue Origin於2000年開業），布蘭遜巧妙地確保維珍銀河是第一間上市的太空旅遊公司。去年，維珍銀河與已經上市的空殼公司Social Capital Hedosophia Holdings反向合併，成功登陸紐約證交所。<br />\n<br />\n<span class=\"red\">如此一來，布蘭遜不但可以自誇擁有「第一間上市的純航天公司」， 他還可以獲得一種獨特貨幣&mdash;&mdash;維珍銀河的股份，這是馬斯克（Elon Musk）麾下SpaceX及貝佐斯（Jeff Bezos）麾下Blue Origin等競爭對手無法取得的。</span><br />\n<br />\n現在，<span class=\"red\">維珍銀河基本上可以隨心所欲地發行新股，讓公司自行創造現金流來支持業務，直至付費客戶能夠接手這個角色為止</span>。出售維珍銀河股份所得的資金有朝一日也可以扶助新的事業，例如<br />\n<br />\n將乘客送到軌道上的太空酒店（Axiom Space正在建造一間這樣的酒店）；<br />\n<br />\n在地球上進行「點對點」的商業飛行（這是摩根士丹利對維珍銀河股票的重要買入理據之一）；或<br />\n<br />\n其他真正造福人群的業務，例如向其他星球發射火箭，為地球上的科學家拍照（維珍姊妹公司維珍軌道正準備要這樣做）。<br />\n<br />\n儘管這麼做可能有違布蘭遜的作風，但他可能還會在其他航天初創企業發展到足以和維珍銀河競爭之前，就利用維珍銀河的股票將它們一一收購。例如，競爭對手Blue Origin正在探索其他將遊客送到太空的方法，Rocket Lab則使用小型火箭將更小的衛星送入軌道，但直到這些公司實現盈利（或至少上市）之前，它們都很容易被維珍銀河這樣的公司收購。基本上，維珍銀河能夠以高價配股形式「印銀紙」，並在其他航天公司倒閉之前，扮演白武士打救它們。<br />\n<br />\n所以，是的，雖然維珍銀河的未來無法預料，但筆者確實看到了一條出路，<span class=\"red\">假以時日可以把維珍銀河變成一間傘形公司，並在未來幾十年成為航天界的主導力量。</span><br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2lny/donno.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2lny/donno.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2lny/donno.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2lny/donno.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2lny/donno.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2lny/donno.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"4f70c5cc1ba36e96107e6ea39f63aedfcd08388c","tid":2423268,"uid":177089,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-02-25T23:57:10.000Z","msg":"妖股<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/dying.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/dying.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/dying.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/dying.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"5fd1f477e006298f473e1060853c5988fce801da","tid":2423268,"uid":125070,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-02-26T00:04:10.000Z","msg":"60冇走 一唔試飛<br />\n53.5走一半 48走埋成本果一半<br />\n執返身彩 但出面都係咁跌市<br />\n咩科技股都死 其實避唔到<br />\n<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/dying.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/dying.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/dying.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"23f58f9865f568c4e49e28ab173346165a5fdc3d","tid":2423268,"uid":177089,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-02-26T00:12:35.000Z","msg":"Virgin Galactic Delays Test Flight Further As New Snag Uncovered<br />\n<br />\n<br />\nVirgin Galactic (SPCE) scheduled its next test flight for May as the space tourism company fixes an issue that was discovered earlier this month. SPCE stock fell.<br />\n<br />\n The May flight would come about three months after the company opened a window for another attempt at a powered test flight of its SpaceShipTwo vehicle.<br />\n<br />\n<span class=\"red\">Virgin Galactic said it's completing modifications and conducting technical checks ahead of the flight, which will include revenue-generating payloads as part of the NASA Flight Opportunities Program.</span><br />\n<br />\nLate Thursday, the company said it uncovered additional electromagnetic interference issues during preflight preparations for its Feb. 13 flight. It will take about nine weeks to resolve. A modification to the flight control computer is being prototyped now and testing on the part can start.<br />\n<br />\nThe December test flight was supposed to complete data-gathering for the final two FAA verification and validation milestones. The next attempt will try to capture that data and evaluate the upgraded horizontal stabilizers and flight controls.<br />\n<span class=\"red\"><br />\nVirgin Galactic had hoped to see its first commercial flight in Q1 2021, but the latest delays put that well into Q2 at the soonest.<br />\n<br />\nIf the retest is successful, the company has said it plans a second powered flight, a key step needed before revenue-generating commercial flights can start.</span><br />\n<br />\n<span class=\"red\">On Thursday, the company also said significant milestones on a second spaceship have been completed ahead of a scheduled rollout on March 30. Virgin Galactic is also accelerating enhancements to the Eve mothership vehicle, which carries SpaceShipTwo before it's released, and is preparing for second-generation mothership program.<br />\n<br />\nMeanwhile, the Italian Air Force will fly three passengers and multiple payloads on a Virgin Galactic flight in late summer or early fall, generating revenue for the company.</span><br />\n<br />\nWall Street has been exceptionally bullish on the stock despite the lack of revenue-generating flights. But SPCE stock was downgraded to neutral from buy by UBS earlier this month as analysts think that a successful test flight by Virgin Galactic is already priced into its shares."},{"pid":"aa68a5750afbea053707ec68ea9eb448bcc5acd0","tid":2423268,"uid":172454,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-02-26T00:16:43.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />本來隻嘢就係冇價值冇實力<br />\n利伸 7蚊果陣買過"}]}